To avoid common errors when implementing recursive functions, you can follow these best practices:

### 1. Define a Clear Base Case

**Tip**: Always clearly define a base case that provides a stopping condition for the recursion. Ensure that it handles all edge cases.

**Example**:
```java
public static int factorial(int n) {
    // Base case: Factorial of 0 is 1
    if (n == 0) {
        return 1;
    }
    return n * factorial(n - 1);
}
```

